T1  - Say on Pay Votes and CEO Compensation: Evidence from the UK*
PY  - 2013
Y1  - 2013/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfs003
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 17
IS  - 2
SP  - 527
EP  - 563
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - We examine the effect of say on pay regulation in the UK. Consistent with the view that shareholders regard say on pay as a value-creating mechanism, the regulation’s announcement triggered a positive stock price reaction at firms with weak penalties for poor performance. UK firms responded to negative say on pay voting outcomes by removing controversial CEO pay practices criticized as rewards for failure (e.g., generous severance contracts) and increasing the sensitivity of pay to poor realizations of performance.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfs003
ER  - 



